data.content:
**In .NET 11, all synchronous I/O on the EF Core Cosmos DB provider is fully removed — no opt-in can restore it.** Your .NET 10 `sync-over-async` configuration is ignored; every call to `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` will **throw at runtime**.

You must convert everything to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will cascade — all callers of these methods must also become `async`/`await` up the call chain. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
